26/10/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The United States has decided to keep a small residual force in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) after the EU's takeover of the peacekeeping mission in December, NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer said Monday (25 October).
The US troops would be stationed near Tuzla.
In other news, Bosnian Serb President Dragan Cavic said Monday that Republika Srpska would follow the EU's lead and freeze the assets of Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic.
The Union's foreign ministers decided on 11 October to freeze the assets of the two Bosnian Serb leaders and Croatian fugitive Ante Gotovina.
(FT, Nezavisne novine - 26/10/04;
Fena, AFP, Pincom.info - 25/10/04)
